itting process; TableCurve 3D, a surface fitter with the ability to find the ideal equation to describe three-dimensional empirical data; and micro-electromechanical systems (MEMS), a technology to create electronic storage devices. In addition, it offers crane engineering and business analytics services. The company's products are used by scientists and engineers in various fields, including medical research, environmental sciences, geo sciences, chemistry, aerospace, biotech, telecommunication, automotive, physics, life sciences, quality control, biology, materials characteristics, pathology, engineering, and in other fields. Cranes Software International Limited was founded in 1991 and is headquartered in Bengaluru, India."}}